ActAppropriation Act No. 2, 2003-2004
Appropriation Act No. 2, 2003-2004
PrecisAppointment of ALEXANDRA BUGAILISKIS as Ambassador of Canada to the Republic of Cuba; LORENZ FRIEDLAENDER as Ambassador of Canada to the Kingdom of Sweden; LAURETTE GLASGOW as Consul General of Canada in the Principality of Monaco; LOUIS GUAY as Ambassador of Canada to the Gabonese Republic; JOHN T. HOLMES as Ambassador of Canada to the Hashemite Kingdom of Jordan; JEAN-PIERRE JUNEAU as Ambassador of Canada to the North Atlantic Council; BRUCE JUTZI as Ambassador of Canada to the Czech Republic; RICHARD KOHLER as Consul General of Canada at Sydney (Commonwealth of Australia); SUZANNE LAPORTE as Ambassador of Canada to the Federative Republic of Brazil; RANDOLPH MANK as Ambassador of Canada to the Republic of Indonesia; PAUL MEYER as Alternate Permanent Representative and Ambassador of Canada to the Office of the United Nations, and Permanent Representative and Ambassador to the United Nations for Disarmament; MALCOLM McKECHNIE as Consul General of Canada at Atlanta (United States of America); RICHARD TÊTU as Ambassador of Canada to the Republic of Iceland; CLAUDIO VALLE as High Commissioner for Canada in Jamaica, with concurrent accreditation to Belize; CHRISTOPHER WESTDAL as Ambassador of Canada to the Russian Federation; and SHELLEY WHITING as Ambassador of Canada to Bosnia and Herzegovina.
